At first, I was gonna use a Tinker Toy to
hold the pick up. And I tuned this little

00:30:53.909 --> 00:30:59.380
thing like a hammer dulcimer and it had a
pretty good sound. And then I wanted to move

00:30:59.380 --> 00:31:04.409
on to making a genuine cigar box guitar. These
have been around for over a hundred years

00:31:04.409 --> 00:31:09.269
and Helen Wolfe got started on one and Jimi
Hendrix got started on a cigar box guitar.

00:31:09.269 --> 00:31:13.830
And I bought fret wire. I was always afraid
frets would be so hard to install, but they're

00:31:13.830 --> 00:31:18.230
really easy actually because of the -- see,
