00:34:28.310 --> 00:34:37.070
Another thing I wanted to do was add a temperature
control to my espresso maker. This is a Rancilio

00:34:37.070 --> 00:34:42.210
SILVIA espresso maker; they cost about 500
to 600 dollars. They're really great espresso

00:34:42.210 --> 00:34:47.960
machines. The weak â€“ the Achilles heel of
them is that they use the bi-metallic thermostat

00:34:47.960 --> 00:34:54.801
that's just an on/off thermostat and so, you
can have a temperature swing of like, 40 degrees

00:34:54.801 --> 00:35:01.750
Fahrenheit when you make â€“ when you pull
a shot of espresso and that's completely unacceptable.

00:35:01.750 --> 00:35:05.980
You really should lock it down a lot tighter
than that and so, people have come up with

00:35:05.980 --> 00:35:10.000
these things called temperature surfing, where
they wait 'til the light goes off, they pour

00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:13.180
some water, they listen for the hiss to stop,
that means it stopped boiling. You continue

00:35:13.180 --> 00:35:18.400
to let the water pour off for a while, then
you pack -- put the coffee on. But the other

00:35:18.400 --> 00:35:25.140
way is that you can use a PID temperature
controller on it-- proportional integral derivative

00:35:25.140 --> 00:35:31.800
temperature controller, that does a lot -- is
a much more sophisticated way of controlling

00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:40.030
it. And people are actually now selling kits
that you can attach and they come with a relay

00:35:40.030 --> 00:35:41.260
to turn the boiler off and on.

00:35:41.260 --> 00:35:50.170
So, I took my espresso maker apart, took the
connectors off the bi-metallic thermostat

00:35:50.170 --> 00:35:57.511
and that's what it looks like now. That unit
there, on the left, is the temperature controller

00:35:57.511 --> 00:36:01.830
and you can use little push buttons to set
the exact temperature you want the water to

00:36:01.830 --> 00:36:07.050
be. And that's actually the outside of the
boiler; the water temperature is lower than

00:36:07.050 --> 00:36:12.440
that. That would not be good coffee like that.
And so anyway, it's much better coffee. I've

00:36:12.440 --> 00:36:16.950
locked that down; the temperature variation
is like, under one degree now as opposed to

00:36:16.950 --> 00:36:18.210
40 degrees.

