00:45:22.030 --> 00:45:28.850
glue and filled in the cut, the misplaced
slot, and it still looked bad. So then, I

00:45:28.850 --> 00:45:31.890
thought, "Well, I'll just paint the whole
thing a color." And I painted it light green

00:45:31.890 --> 00:45:36.540
and it ended up being like a cool thing and
now, I typically paint all my necks a color,

00:45:36.540 --> 00:45:41.490
as my thing. That's my thing is to have colored
necks. And if I hadn't have failed in that

00:45:41.490 --> 00:45:44.500
way, I probably never would have painted the
necks that way.

00:45:44.500 --> 00:45:50.190
So sometimes they lead to places you wouldn't
have taken yourself intentionally, in a good

00:45:50.190 --> 00:45:51.190
way.

00:45:51.190 --> 00:45:55.460
&gt;&gt;Male audience #3: So, that dovetails in
with the other question I have, which is when

00:45:55.460 --> 00:45:59.740
you're building a cigar box guitar, how the
hell do you brace the neck on there? Do you

00:45:59.740 --> 00:46:05.070
not just rip the box apart when you put the
tension on from the strings?

00:46:05.070 --> 00:46:11.630
&gt;&gt;Mark Frauenfelder: Oh, yeah. What I do is
I just open the lid of the cigar, so here's

00:46:11.630 --> 00:46:20.020
the box and here's the lid. I open the lid
and then I just lay the stick on it and then

00:46:20.020 --> 00:46:24.731
close it and then, let's see. I mean--

00:46:24.731 --> 00:46:26.330
&gt;&gt;Male audience #3: I see the neck goes all
the way through it.

00:46:26.330 --> 00:46:29.660
&gt;&gt;Mark Frauenfelder: Yeah, the neck goes all
the way through. And then I just drill, I

00:46:29.660 --> 00:46:33.430
don't use glue when I put them together; I
use screws. I try to use as little glue as

00:46:33.430 --> 00:46:37.210
possible on anything cause then you can take
it apart if it breaks and you don't have to

00:46:37.210 --> 00:46:38.790
wait for the glue to dry.

00:46:38.790 --> 00:46:42.260
So yeah, there's not a problem with it, but
I see what you mean. Otherwise you would have

00:46:42.260 --> 00:46:46.251
a problem. It goes all the way through. And
it's thinner there, though, because you want

00:46:46.251 --> 00:46:50.340
more resonance. You make it as, it's like
a game. The part that's hidden inside the

00:46:50.340 --> 00:46:58.230
box, you want, I think, as thin as possible
